WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:18.520
Beauty and the Beast by Jean-Marie LeCranz de Beaumont Copyright Black Cat Publishing

00:30.000 --> 00:36.720
1. Beauty's Family

00:36.720 --> 00:41.000
A rich man lives in a big city near the sea.

00:41.000 --> 00:45.080
He has got three daughters and three sons.

00:45.080 --> 00:51.080
One daughter is called Beauty because she is very beautiful.

00:51.080 --> 00:56.560
The other two daughters are called Rosalind and Hortensia.

00:56.800 --> 01:00.280
They are lazy and unfriendly.

01:00.280 --> 01:03.400
They like going out and having fun.

01:03.400 --> 01:07.640
They both want to find a rich husband.

01:07.640 --> 01:12.320
They do not like beauty because she is beautiful.

01:12.320 --> 01:15.320
Beauty has got long red hair.

01:15.320 --> 01:18.240
She is kind and friendly.

01:18.240 --> 01:21.720
She likes staying at home and reading books.

01:21.720 --> 01:25.320
She also likes playing the piano.

01:25.320 --> 01:28.280
Beauty's father is a merchant.

01:28.280 --> 01:34.360
One day he loses all his money because his ship is lost at sea.

01:34.360 --> 01:36.400
My dear children.

01:36.400 --> 01:38.160
He says sadly.

01:38.160 --> 01:40.720
I haven't got much money.

01:40.720 --> 01:42.720
We're poor.

01:42.720 --> 01:48.000
We must leave this big house and go and live in the country.

01:48.000 --> 01:50.280
Oh dear.

01:50.280 --> 01:52.240
Say the two sisters.

01:52.240 --> 01:53.800
We are poor.

01:53.800 --> 01:56.560
This is terrible.

01:56.560 --> 01:58.920
What bad luck.

01:58.920 --> 02:01.800
Say the three brothers.

02:01.800 --> 02:04.000
We have to work now.

02:04.000 --> 02:06.440
Says Beauty's father.

02:06.440 --> 02:08.240
Work.

02:08.240 --> 02:10.760
Say the two sisters.

02:10.760 --> 02:11.680
No.

02:11.680 --> 02:13.880
We don't want to work.

02:13.880 --> 02:17.320
And we don't want to live in the country.

02:17.320 --> 02:19.320
They start to cry.

02:19.320 --> 02:28.800
Beauty is sad but she says let's not cry.

02:28.800 --> 02:33.040
We can work and be happy without money.

02:33.040 --> 02:38.080
The family goes to the country and lives in a small house.

02:38.080 --> 02:43.240
Beauty gets up at four o'clock every morning to clean the house and cook.

02:43.240 --> 02:46.920
Then she washes the family's clothes in the river.

02:47.000 --> 02:50.440
The three brothers work in the country.

02:50.440 --> 02:53.640
Rosalind and Hortensia do not work.

02:53.640 --> 02:56.520
They do nothing all day.

02:56.520 --> 03:01.040
They sleep all morning and walk in the woods in the afternoon.

03:01.040 --> 03:03.520
I'm unhappy.

03:03.520 --> 03:04.520
Says Rosalind.

03:04.520 --> 03:09.960
I don't like the country because there's nothing to do.

03:09.960 --> 03:14.720
We can't go to the theatre and wear nice clothes.

03:15.720 --> 03:18.720
And we haven't got any friends.

03:18.720 --> 03:20.720
Look at Beauty.

03:20.720 --> 03:22.720
Says Rosalind angrily.

03:22.720 --> 03:27.720
She works and she's happy in this terrible place.

03:27.720 --> 03:30.720
Beauty's father says.

03:30.720 --> 03:32.720
Dear Beauty.

03:32.720 --> 03:35.720
You work a lot and you're always happy.

03:35.720 --> 03:37.720
You're a wonderful daughter.

03:37.720 --> 03:44.720
Listening activity.

03:44.720 --> 03:47.720
Here is an example.

03:47.720 --> 03:51.720
What does Rosalind want to buy for the summer?

03:51.720 --> 03:55.720
I want to buy a new red hat for the summer.

03:55.720 --> 03:58.720
But you have already got a pink one.

03:58.720 --> 04:01.720
What about a nice blue hat?

04:01.720 --> 04:02.720
No.

04:02.720 --> 04:05.720
I like red.

04:06.720 --> 04:08.720
One.

04:08.720 --> 04:13.720
Which shop is next to Marie's hat shop?

04:13.720 --> 04:18.720
Well, let's go to Marie's hat shop.

04:18.720 --> 04:21.720
Is the shop near the park?

04:21.720 --> 04:22.720
No.

04:22.720 --> 04:24.720
It's next to the bakery.

04:24.720 --> 04:26.720
Oh, I remember.

04:26.720 --> 04:29.720
Opposite the library.

04:29.720 --> 04:31.720
Two.

04:32.720 --> 04:37.720
What does Rosalind want to buy at the bakery?

04:37.720 --> 04:39.720
Oh, good.

04:39.720 --> 04:42.720
Then we can buy some chocolate biscuits at the bakery.

04:42.720 --> 04:44.720
I love them.

04:44.720 --> 04:45.720
Me too.

04:45.720 --> 04:50.720
I like chocolate cake and chocolate biscuits.

04:50.720 --> 04:53.720
Do we need to get some bread too?

04:53.720 --> 04:55.720
I don't think so.

04:55.720 --> 04:59.720
There is lots of bread at home.

04:59.720 --> 05:01.720
Three.

05:01.720 --> 05:07.720
What time does Marie's hat shop open on Saturdays?

05:07.720 --> 05:10.720
What time does the hat shop open?

05:10.720 --> 05:18.720
It usually opens at nine, but today is Saturday and it opens at half past nine.

05:18.720 --> 05:23.720
We must wait for fifteen minutes then.

05:23.720 --> 05:25.720
Four.

05:25.720 --> 05:30.720
What does Hortensia want to buy for the party?

05:30.720 --> 05:33.720
Let's put our coats on and go.

05:33.720 --> 05:34.720
Okay.

05:34.720 --> 05:41.720
Today I want to buy some new white shoes to wear with my white dress for the party.

05:41.720 --> 05:50.720
But you have already got nine pairs of white shoes.

05:50.720 --> 05:52.720
Chapter two.

05:52.720 --> 05:56.720
Beauty's Rose.

05:56.720 --> 06:01.720
A year later, Beauty's father gets an important letter.

06:01.720 --> 06:04.720
He calls his six children and says,

06:04.720 --> 06:07.720
Listen to this letter.

06:07.720 --> 06:09.720
Your ship is here.

06:09.720 --> 06:12.720
It is not lost at sea.

06:12.720 --> 06:14.720
Please come to the port.

06:14.720 --> 06:17.720
Everyone is happy.

06:17.720 --> 06:19.720
This is wonderful news.

06:19.720 --> 06:21.720
Say the three sons.

06:21.720 --> 06:22.720
Yes.

06:22.720 --> 06:24.720
Says their father.

06:24.720 --> 06:28.720
The ship with my goods is in the port.

06:28.720 --> 06:30.720
We're rich again.

06:30.720 --> 06:31.720
Says Rosalind.

06:31.720 --> 06:34.720
We can buy beautiful clothes.

06:34.720 --> 06:38.720
We can go back to our big house in the city.

06:38.720 --> 06:41.720
Says Hortensia.

06:41.720 --> 06:43.720
I must go to the port today.

06:43.720 --> 06:46.720
Says her father happily.

06:47.720 --> 06:49.720
Oh father.

06:49.720 --> 06:51.720
Says Hortensia.

06:51.720 --> 06:56.720
Bring me some new clothes and new hats.

06:56.720 --> 06:57.720
Yes.

06:57.720 --> 06:58.720
Says Rosalind.

06:58.720 --> 07:02.720
And some new shoes and jewels.

07:02.720 --> 07:05.720
Beauty's father looks at her and says,

07:05.720 --> 07:08.720
What do you want, Beauty?

07:08.720 --> 07:11.720
Please, don't spend your money, Father.

07:11.720 --> 07:12.720
Says Beauty.

07:12.720 --> 07:15.720
Just bring me a rose.

07:15.720 --> 07:19.720
Beauty's father gets to the port and finds his ship.

07:19.720 --> 07:22.720
But there are no goods on it.

07:22.720 --> 07:24.720
It is empty.

07:24.720 --> 07:26.720
What bad luck!

07:26.720 --> 07:28.720
He says angrily.

07:28.720 --> 07:33.720
I must go home and tell the children the bad news.

07:33.720 --> 07:37.720
On the way home he crosses a big forest.

07:37.720 --> 07:40.720
It is snowing and windy.

07:40.720 --> 07:41.720
He is lost.

07:41.720 --> 07:43.720
Where am I?

07:43.720 --> 07:44.720
He thinks.

07:44.720 --> 07:46.720
Where can I go?

07:46.720 --> 07:49.720
I'm very cold and tired.

07:49.720 --> 07:52.720
He hears some wolves and he is afraid.

07:52.720 --> 07:56.720
Suddenly he sees a big castle in the forest.

07:56.720 --> 07:59.720
And there are lights in the windows.

07:59.720 --> 08:00.720
Oh good.

08:00.720 --> 08:01.720
He thinks.

08:01.720 --> 08:05.720
Perhaps the people in the castle can help me.

08:05.720 --> 08:09.720
He takes his horse to the stable near the castle.

08:09.720 --> 08:13.720
He knocks on the big door of the castle but no one answers.

08:13.720 --> 08:16.720
He waits outside the door.

08:16.720 --> 08:21.720
Then he opens the door and goes inside.

08:21.720 --> 08:24.720
He sees a big hall with a fireplace.

08:24.720 --> 08:28.720
There is a long table with a lot of food on it.

08:28.720 --> 08:33.720
He is cold and sits near the fireplace.

08:33.720 --> 08:35.720
How strange!

08:35.720 --> 08:36.720
He thinks.

08:36.720 --> 08:39.720
There's no one here.

08:39.720 --> 08:44.720
He is hungry and sits down at the table and starts to eat.

08:44.720 --> 08:46.720
Then he is sleepy.

08:46.720 --> 08:51.720
He finds a warm, comfortable bed and falls asleep.

08:51.720 --> 08:56.720
The next morning he finds some new clothes near his bed.

08:56.720 --> 08:58.720
How nice.

08:58.720 --> 09:00.720
New clothes.

09:00.720 --> 09:01.720
He thinks.

09:01.720 --> 09:05.720
A kind person lives in this castle.

09:05.720 --> 09:09.720
He looks out of the window and is surprised.

09:09.720 --> 09:13.720
It's not snowing and it's a beautiful day.

09:13.720 --> 09:15.720
He thinks.

09:15.720 --> 09:18.720
And there are flowers in the garden.

09:18.720 --> 09:21.720
He gets dressed and goes to the hall.

09:21.720 --> 09:25.720
There are biscuits, chocolate and milk on the long table.

09:25.720 --> 09:27.720
He sits down and says.

09:27.720 --> 09:31.720
Thank you for this lovely breakfast.

09:31.720 --> 09:34.720
He looks round but sees no one.

09:34.720 --> 09:37.720
He eats and decides to go home.

09:37.720 --> 09:40.720
He goes to the stable and gets his horse.

09:40.720 --> 09:44.720
In the garden he sees some roses.

09:44.720 --> 09:46.720
Beauty wants a rose.

09:46.720 --> 09:47.720
He thinks.

09:47.720 --> 09:50.720
He takes a lovely one.

09:50.720 --> 09:53.720
Suddenly he hears a terrible noise.

09:57.720 --> 10:02.720
He turns round and sees an ugly monster.

10:05.720 --> 10:08.720
Listening activity.

10:08.720 --> 10:10.720
Here is an example.

10:10.720 --> 10:15.720
Where does beauty's father's ship come from?

10:15.720 --> 10:17.720
Good morning.

10:17.720 --> 10:20.720
Can you help me? I'm looking for my ship.

10:20.720 --> 10:24.720
There are eleven ships in the port this morning.

10:24.720 --> 10:26.720
What's the name of the ship?

10:26.720 --> 10:28.720
I don't know.

10:28.720 --> 10:31.720
It's a big ship and it comes from Italy.

10:31.720 --> 10:33.720
There are two big ships in the port.

10:33.720 --> 10:37.720
One from England and another from Turkey.

10:37.720 --> 10:42.720
No. My ship is from Italy.

10:42.720 --> 10:47.720
One. What is the ship like?

10:47.720 --> 10:51.720
Oh, perhaps you're looking for the blue one.

10:51.720 --> 10:54.720
No. The ship is red and black.

10:54.720 --> 10:56.720
Now I remember.

10:56.720 --> 11:01.720
It's near the black ship from Turkey.

11:01.720 --> 11:05.720
Two. Who is the captain of the ship?

11:05.720 --> 11:09.720
Good. Who is the captain of the ship?

11:09.720 --> 11:15.720
I don't know his name, but he is a young man with brown hair.

11:15.720 --> 11:17.720
Does he wear glasses?

11:17.720 --> 11:20.720
Yes, he does.

11:20.720 --> 11:22.720
Three.

11:22.720 --> 11:26.720
What time does the captain go to his ship?

11:26.720 --> 11:30.720
What time does he usually come here?

11:30.720 --> 11:36.720
He usually comes very early, at half past six in the morning,

11:36.720 --> 11:39.720
and he goes to his office.

11:39.720 --> 11:45.720
Then, at eight o'clock, he goes to his ship.

11:45.720 --> 11:51.720
Four. How does he usually travel to work?

11:51.720 --> 11:54.720
Does he ride his horse to work in the morning?

11:54.720 --> 11:58.720
Well, he usually comes by boat.

11:58.720 --> 12:03.720
He sometimes comes here on foot in summer.

12:03.720 --> 12:06.720
Thank you.

12:09.720 --> 12:12.720
Castle's.

12:12.720 --> 12:14.720
What is a castle?

12:14.720 --> 12:19.720
A castle is the home of a king or a very rich family.

12:19.720 --> 12:23.720
It protects the people who live there.

12:23.720 --> 12:31.720
Castle's have got high walls and small windows, so they are difficult to attack.

12:31.720 --> 12:40.720
Castle's are usually near rivers, near the sea, on hills or on mountains.

12:40.720 --> 12:44.720
History of castles.

12:44.720 --> 12:51.720
In the 10th century, people build small wooden castles in Europe.

12:51.720 --> 12:56.720
In 1066, William the Conqueror attacks England.

12:56.720 --> 13:00.720
He is from Normandy in France.

13:00.720 --> 13:05.720
He builds the first big stone castles in England.

13:05.720 --> 13:11.720
He builds the Tower of London in about 1078.

13:11.720 --> 13:17.720
The Normans build about 80 stone castles in England.

13:17.720 --> 13:23.720
There are a lot of stone castles in Europe in the 12th and 13th centuries.

13:23.720 --> 13:28.720
They are big, and they can protect a lot of people.

13:28.720 --> 13:33.720
Let's look at some important castles in Europe.

13:33.720 --> 13:38.720
Bodeum Castle, East Sussex, England.

13:38.720 --> 13:46.720
This is an old medieval castle with big square walls and a moat around it.

13:47.720 --> 13:50.720
Clams Castle, Scotland.

13:50.720 --> 13:57.720
This big castle has got a long history of ghosts and terrible secrets.

13:57.720 --> 14:02.720
It has got more than 100 rooms.

14:02.720 --> 14:06.720
Shenonso Castle, France.

14:06.720 --> 14:12.720
Shenonso Castle is on the Cher River in the famous Loire Valley.

14:12.720 --> 14:18.720
There are a lot of beautiful castles in this valley.

14:18.720 --> 14:22.720
Neuschwanstein Castle, Germany.

14:22.720 --> 14:27.720
This castle is like a picture in a fairy tale book.

14:27.720 --> 14:37.720
King Ludwig II built it in 1869 as his home.

14:37.720 --> 14:42.720
Chapter 3, The Beast.

14:42.720 --> 14:45.720
You're a bad man.

14:45.720 --> 14:47.720
Crys the Beast angrily.

14:47.720 --> 14:52.720
You come to my castle and I save your life.

14:52.720 --> 14:55.720
You eat here and you sleep here.

14:55.720 --> 14:59.720
And then you take one of my beautiful roses.

14:59.720 --> 15:02.720
For this you must die.

15:02.720 --> 15:05.720
Beauty's father starts to cry.

15:05.720 --> 15:08.720
Oh, sir, I'm sorry.

15:08.720 --> 15:10.720
You're very kind.

15:10.720 --> 15:13.720
Please don't be angry with me.

15:13.720 --> 15:16.720
This rose is for one of my daughters.

15:16.720 --> 15:19.720
My name is not, sir.

15:19.720 --> 15:21.720
It is Beast.

15:21.720 --> 15:24.720
Please call me by my name.

15:24.720 --> 15:27.720
You talk about your daughters.

15:27.720 --> 15:31.720
Then one of your daughters must die in your place.

15:31.720 --> 15:33.720
Oh no!

15:33.720 --> 15:35.720
There's Beauty's father.

15:35.720 --> 15:38.720
They're young and they don't want to die.

15:38.720 --> 15:41.720
Then you must come back here and die.

15:41.720 --> 15:43.720
Says the Beast.

15:43.720 --> 15:46.720
I can wait three months.

15:46.720 --> 15:49.720
Do you agree to come back?

15:49.720 --> 15:52.720
Beauty's father agrees to come back.

15:52.720 --> 15:54.720
My daughters must not die.

15:54.720 --> 15:55.720
He thinks.

15:55.720 --> 16:00.720
I want to go home and see my children for the last time.

16:00.720 --> 16:05.720
Before Beauty's father leaves the castle, the Beast talks to him.

16:05.720 --> 16:08.720
I'm not bad.

16:08.720 --> 16:10.720
Says the Beast.

16:10.720 --> 16:12.720
Go back to your bedroom.

16:12.720 --> 16:15.720
There is a big chest there.

16:15.720 --> 16:18.720
Fill it with everything you want.

16:18.720 --> 16:21.720
And it is yours.

16:21.720 --> 16:25.720
Beauty's father fills the chest with a lot of gold.

16:25.720 --> 16:28.720
Then he gets on his horse and goes home.

16:28.720 --> 16:32.720
When he is at home, he gives the rose to Beauty.

16:32.720 --> 16:35.720
Take this rose, Beauty.

16:35.720 --> 16:37.720
He says sadly.

16:37.720 --> 16:41.720
Let me tell you about my terrible adventure.

16:41.720 --> 16:49.720
He tells his children about the empty ship in the port, the castle in the forest and the Beast.

16:49.720 --> 16:52.720
Rosalind and Hortensia are angry with Beauty.

16:52.720 --> 16:54.720
They say...

16:54.720 --> 16:57.720
Father must die because you like roses.

16:57.720 --> 16:59.720
Beauty.

16:59.720 --> 17:00.720
No.

17:00.720 --> 17:01.720
Says Beauty.

17:01.720 --> 17:04.720
Father is not going to die.

17:04.720 --> 17:07.720
I'm going to the Beast's castle.

17:07.720 --> 17:09.720
No, dear sister.

17:09.720 --> 17:11.720
Say her three brothers.

17:11.720 --> 17:15.720
We are going to his castle and we're going to kill him.

17:15.720 --> 17:16.720
No.

17:16.720 --> 17:17.720
That's not possible.

17:17.720 --> 17:19.720
Says their father.

17:19.720 --> 17:22.720
The Beast is very big and strong.

17:22.720 --> 17:26.720
I'm old. I must go and die.

17:26.720 --> 17:29.720
But Beauty does not agree.

17:29.720 --> 17:33.720
She decides to go to the Beast's castle.

17:33.720 --> 17:34.720
No father.

17:34.720 --> 17:35.720
She says.

17:35.720 --> 17:39.720
You must not go. I want to go.

17:39.720 --> 17:41.720
Never my dear Beauty.

17:41.720 --> 17:42.720
Says her father.

17:42.720 --> 17:44.720
I'm not afraid.

17:44.720 --> 17:45.720
Says Beauty.

17:45.720 --> 17:49.720
You must live and look after my brothers and sisters.

17:49.720 --> 17:51.720
They need you.

17:51.720 --> 17:54.720
Beauty's father thinks for a moment.

17:54.720 --> 17:57.720
Then he says sadly.

17:57.720 --> 17:59.720
All right, Beauty.

17:59.720 --> 18:01.720
You can go.

18:01.720 --> 18:05.720
Beauty's brothers are very sad.

18:05.720 --> 18:08.720
But Hortensia and Rosalind are not.

18:08.720 --> 18:13.720
The next morning, Beauty and her father go to the Beast's castle.

18:13.720 --> 18:19.720
Inside the castle, they see a long table with a lot of good food on it.

18:20.720 --> 18:25.720
Beauty and her father are not hungry, but they sit down and eat.

18:25.720 --> 18:28.720
Suddenly, they hear a loud noise.

18:32.720 --> 18:34.720
What's that terrible noise?

18:34.720 --> 18:35.720
Asks Beauty.

18:35.720 --> 18:37.720
The Beast is coming.

18:37.720 --> 18:39.720
Says her father.

18:39.720 --> 18:44.720
Beauty sees the Beast's ugly face and she is terrified.

18:45.720 --> 18:49.720
Oh, this Beast is really terrible, she thinks.

18:49.720 --> 18:52.720
The Beast looks at her and says.

18:52.720 --> 18:55.720
You're a brave girl.

18:55.720 --> 18:59.720
I'm very sorry about the rose from your garden.

18:59.720 --> 19:02.720
Says Beauty quietly.

19:02.720 --> 19:06.720
The Beast looks at Beauty's father and says.

19:06.720 --> 19:09.720
You must go away tomorrow.

19:09.720 --> 19:12.720
And don't come back.

19:12.720 --> 19:15.720
Do you understand?

19:15.720 --> 19:20.720
Beauty's father looks at the Beast and then at his daughter.

19:20.720 --> 19:21.720
Oh, Beauty.

19:21.720 --> 19:22.720
He says.

19:22.720 --> 19:24.720
Please go home.

19:24.720 --> 19:26.720
Let me stay here.

19:26.720 --> 19:28.720
No, Father.

19:28.720 --> 19:29.720
Says Beauty.

19:29.720 --> 19:31.720
We must be brave.

19:31.720 --> 19:33.720
We're both tired.

19:33.720 --> 19:35.720
Let's go and sleep now.

19:35.720 --> 19:39.720
Tomorrow morning, you can go home to my brothers and sisters.

19:40.720 --> 19:43.720
That night, Beauty has a dream.

19:43.720 --> 19:46.720
In her dream, a good fairy says.

19:46.720 --> 19:49.720
You're a good girl, Beauty.

19:49.720 --> 19:51.720
And you've got a kind heart.

19:51.720 --> 19:54.720
You want to save your father's life.

19:54.720 --> 19:57.720
You're going to be very happy one day.

20:02.720 --> 20:03.720
Chapter 4.

20:03.720 --> 20:07.720
Life at the Castle.

20:07.720 --> 20:11.720
The next morning, Beauty's father leaves the castle.

20:11.720 --> 20:13.720
He is crying.

20:13.720 --> 20:15.720
Don't cry, Father.

20:15.720 --> 20:16.720
Says Beauty.

20:16.720 --> 20:19.720
Remember, I love you.

20:19.720 --> 20:21.720
Goodbye.

20:21.720 --> 20:22.720
Dear Beauty.

20:22.720 --> 20:24.720
Says her father.

20:24.720 --> 20:26.720
Beauty is terrified.

20:26.720 --> 20:29.720
The Beast is going to eat me tonight.

20:29.720 --> 20:30.720
She thinks.

20:30.720 --> 20:33.720
I want to enjoy my last day.

20:33.720 --> 20:37.720
I'm going to visit the garden of the castle.

20:37.720 --> 20:41.720
She goes to see the big garden and she is surprised.

20:41.720 --> 20:45.720
It is a beautiful garden with a lot of lovely flowers.

20:45.720 --> 20:48.720
Then she goes to see the big castle.

20:48.720 --> 20:51.720
She looks in all the rooms.

20:51.720 --> 20:54.720
On one door, she sees this sign.

20:54.720 --> 20:56.720
Beauty's room.

20:56.720 --> 21:00.720
She opens the door and sees a lovely room.

21:00.720 --> 21:04.720
There is a nice bed and a mirror on the wall.

21:04.720 --> 21:07.720
Beauty looks round and thinks.

21:07.720 --> 21:10.720
There's a piano and a lot of books for me.

21:10.720 --> 21:12.720
How strange.

21:12.720 --> 21:15.720
Perhaps the Beast doesn't want to eat me tonight.

21:15.720 --> 21:19.720
She takes a book and starts to read it.

21:19.720 --> 21:23.720
Suddenly, she sees these words on the pages.

21:23.720 --> 21:25.720
Welcome, Beauty.

21:25.720 --> 21:27.720
Don't be afraid.

21:27.720 --> 21:29.720
You're the Queen here.

21:29.720 --> 21:32.720
Tell me everything you want.

21:32.720 --> 21:35.720
I only want to see my poor father.

21:35.720 --> 21:37.720
Says Beauty.

21:37.720 --> 21:41.720
Suddenly, she sees her father in the mirror on the wall.

21:41.720 --> 21:44.720
He is very sad.

21:44.720 --> 21:49.720
She also sees her home and Hortensia and Rosalind.

21:49.720 --> 21:52.720
They are happy without beauty.

21:52.720 --> 21:54.720
The Beast is kind to me.

21:54.720 --> 21:55.720
She thinks.

21:55.720 --> 21:58.720
Why am I afraid of him?

21:58.720 --> 22:01.720
At twelve o'clock, she has lunch.

22:01.720 --> 22:04.720
After lunch, she goes to her room.

22:04.720 --> 22:07.720
What a beautiful piano.

22:07.720 --> 22:08.720
thinks Beauty.

22:08.720 --> 22:10.720
I want to play it.

22:10.720 --> 22:14.720
She plays some wonderful music on the piano.

22:14.720 --> 22:18.720
Then she looks at all the books in her room.

22:18.720 --> 22:22.720
Some of them have got pictures and others have not.

22:22.720 --> 22:27.720
She takes a book about flowers and looks at the pictures of different flowers.

22:27.720 --> 22:31.720
Then she sees pictures of roses of all colors.

22:31.720 --> 22:36.720
Now I want to go to the garden and look at the lovely roses.

22:36.720 --> 22:38.720
She thinks.

22:38.720 --> 22:42.720
She goes to the garden and stays there all afternoon.

22:42.720 --> 22:46.720
She looks at the flowers and feels happy.

22:46.720 --> 22:53.720
At dinner time, she sits down at the long table and then she hears the Beast coming.

22:53.720 --> 22:56.720
She is terrified.

22:56.720 --> 23:01.720
Beauty, can I sit here with you?

23:01.720 --> 23:02.720
Asks the Beast.

23:02.720 --> 23:06.720
You're the Lord of the Castle, says Beauty.

23:06.720 --> 23:09.720
And you're the Queen.

23:09.720 --> 23:11.720
Says the Beast.

23:11.720 --> 23:14.720
Can I ask you a question?

23:14.720 --> 23:16.720
Yes, of course.

23:16.720 --> 23:19.720
Says Beauty quietly.

23:19.720 --> 23:23.720
Am I very ugly?

23:23.720 --> 23:25.720
Asks the Beast.

23:25.720 --> 23:27.720
Beauty does not know what to say.

23:27.720 --> 23:30.720
She looks at him and thinks for a moment.

23:30.720 --> 23:33.720
Well, yes, you are.

23:33.720 --> 23:34.720
Says Beauty.

23:34.720 --> 23:37.720
But you're kind and polite.

23:37.720 --> 23:40.720
The Beast looks at Beauty and smiles.

23:40.720 --> 23:42.720
You're right.

23:42.720 --> 23:47.720
I'm terribly ugly, but I'm kind.

23:47.720 --> 23:50.720
This is your home now, Beauty.

23:50.720 --> 23:53.720
Please don't be sad.

23:53.720 --> 23:56.720
Some men are handsome, but they're not kind.

23:56.720 --> 23:57.720
Says Beauty.

23:57.720 --> 24:01.720
I prefer you because you've got a good heart.

24:01.720 --> 24:03.720
Thank you, Beauty.

24:03.720 --> 24:05.720
Says the Beast.

24:05.720 --> 24:11.720
Now Beauty is not afraid of the Beast and she eats a big dinner.

24:11.720 --> 24:15.720
The Beast looks at her and asks a question.

24:15.720 --> 24:19.720
Do you want to marry me, Beauty?

24:19.720 --> 24:21.720
What a question.

24:21.720 --> 24:23.720
Beauty is terrified.

24:23.720 --> 24:25.720
What can I say?

24:25.720 --> 24:27.720
Thanks, Beauty.

24:27.720 --> 24:31.720
She is silent for a moment and then she says...

24:31.720 --> 24:36.720
No, I'm sorry, I don't want to marry you.

24:36.720 --> 24:40.720
The Beast is angry and Beauty is afraid.

24:40.720 --> 24:43.720
Then he goes out of the room and says...

24:43.720 --> 24:46.720
Goodbye, Beauty.

24:51.720 --> 24:55.720
Chapter 5, The Magic Ring.

24:55.720 --> 25:00.720
Beauty spends three months at the beautiful castle.

25:00.720 --> 25:03.720
Every day she reads books and plays the piano.

25:03.720 --> 25:07.720
She walks everywhere in the big garden.

25:07.720 --> 25:12.720
She likes the tall trees and the flowers of different colours.

25:12.720 --> 25:16.720
She puts beautiful flowers in the rooms of the castle.

25:16.720 --> 25:20.720
Sometimes she makes perfume from the flowers.

25:20.720 --> 25:25.720
But the days are long and she is often lonely.

25:25.720 --> 25:30.720
Beauty often thinks about her father, her sisters and her brothers.

25:30.720 --> 25:33.720
I want to see my father again.

25:33.720 --> 25:35.720
She thinks sadly.

25:35.720 --> 25:39.720
And I want to see my home again too.

25:39.720 --> 25:45.720
The Beast goes to see her every evening at dinner time at 9 o'clock.

25:45.720 --> 25:49.720
They talk about interesting things and are happy together.

25:49.720 --> 25:53.720
Beauty is not afraid of his ugly face now.

25:53.720 --> 25:58.720
Every evening the Beast asks Beauty the same question.

25:58.720 --> 26:03.720
Beauty, do you want to marry me?

26:03.720 --> 26:06.720
And every evening Beauty answers...

26:06.720 --> 26:08.720
No.

26:08.720 --> 26:10.720
One day Beauty says...

26:10.720 --> 26:14.720
Why do you ask me the same question every evening?

26:14.720 --> 26:18.720
Because I hope to hear a different answer.

26:18.720 --> 26:20.720
Says the Beast.

26:20.720 --> 26:23.720
I'm sorry, I don't want to marry you.

26:23.720 --> 26:25.720
Says Beauty.

26:25.720 --> 26:28.720
The Beast is very sad.

26:28.720 --> 26:31.720
But I'm always going to be your friend.

26:31.720 --> 26:33.720
She says...

26:33.720 --> 26:36.720
You're a wonderful friend.

26:36.720 --> 26:37.720
Says the Beast.

26:37.720 --> 26:39.720
And you are too.

26:39.720 --> 26:42.720
Says Beauty, smiling.

26:42.720 --> 26:45.720
I know I'm terribly ugly.

26:45.720 --> 26:46.720
Says the Beast.

26:46.720 --> 26:48.720
But I love you a lot.

26:48.720 --> 26:50.720
I'm very happy with you.

26:50.720 --> 26:55.720
Please, don't leave me.

26:55.720 --> 27:00.720
Beauty's face becomes red and she is quiet for a moment.

27:00.720 --> 27:02.720
In the mirror of my room.

27:02.720 --> 27:03.720
Says Beauty.

27:03.720 --> 27:05.720
I see my poor father.

27:05.720 --> 27:08.720
He's sad and lonely.

27:08.720 --> 27:10.720
He thinks I'm dead.

27:10.720 --> 27:14.720
My sisters are married and my brothers are away.

27:14.720 --> 27:17.720
I want to see my father for the last time.

27:17.720 --> 27:20.720
Can I go and see him please?

27:20.720 --> 27:21.720
Yes.

27:21.720 --> 27:24.720
You can go and see your father.

27:24.720 --> 27:26.720
Says the Beast.

27:26.720 --> 27:30.720
But I'm going to be very sad without you.

27:30.720 --> 27:32.720
Oh, thank you.

27:32.720 --> 27:34.720
Says Beauty happily.

27:34.720 --> 27:36.720
Please don't be sad Beast.

27:36.720 --> 27:39.720
I'm going to come back in a week.

27:39.720 --> 27:41.720
Says the Beast.

27:41.720 --> 27:44.720
You can visit your father tomorrow morning.

27:44.720 --> 27:48.720
But remember, you must come back in a week.

27:48.720 --> 27:53.720
Before you come back, put this ring on a table near your bed.

27:53.720 --> 27:56.720
It's a magic ring.

27:56.720 --> 28:01.720
Goodbye, Beauty.

28:01.720 --> 28:05.720
Flowers.

28:05.720 --> 28:10.720
There are about 200,000 different kinds of flowers in the world.

28:10.720 --> 28:17.720
Some are very small and others are very big, like the giant rufflesia.

28:17.720 --> 28:21.720
Let's look at some of these flowers.

28:21.720 --> 28:25.720
Flowers that grow in the desert.

28:25.720 --> 28:28.720
Some flowers grow in the desert.

28:28.720 --> 28:32.720
They need hot weather, but they do not need much water.

28:32.720 --> 28:41.720
Some of these flowers are the Apache plume, the desert lily, the yukka, and the prickly pear.

28:41.720 --> 28:44.720
Flowers that grow on water.

28:44.720 --> 28:51.720
Flowers like the lotus, the water lily, and the Louisiana iris grow in water.

28:51.720 --> 28:54.720
These flowers need very warm weather.

28:54.720 --> 28:58.720
You can see them in ponds and lakes.

28:58.720 --> 29:01.720
Tropical flowers.

29:01.720 --> 29:07.720
There are hundreds of beautiful tropical flowers in Hawaii and in the islands of the South Pacific.

29:07.720 --> 29:11.720
Hawaiian orchids are famous everywhere.

29:11.720 --> 29:13.720
Hawaiians make lays.

29:13.720 --> 29:16.720
They are colorful flower necklaces.

29:16.720 --> 29:21.720
They wear them and give them to tourists.

29:21.720 --> 29:24.720
Flowers as decorations.

29:24.720 --> 29:31.720
People use flowers as decorations for festivities like birthdays and weddings.

29:31.720 --> 29:38.720
On St. Valentine's Day, the favorite flower is the red rose.

29:38.720 --> 29:42.720
Flowers in art.

29:42.720 --> 29:46.720
Flowers are the favorite subject of a lot of painters.

29:46.720 --> 29:51.720
Van Gogh, Monet, and Suzanne, all paint flowers.

29:51.720 --> 29:58.720
Van Gogh is famous for sunflowers, and Monet is famous for water lilies.

29:58.720 --> 30:01.720
Flowers we can eat.

30:01.720 --> 30:04.720
Did you know that you can eat flowers?

30:04.720 --> 30:08.720
Some of the vegetables we eat are flowers.

30:08.720 --> 30:13.720
Broccoli, cauliflowers, and artichokes are flower vegetables.

30:13.720 --> 30:18.720
In Japan, people like eating cherry blossom soup.

30:18.720 --> 30:25.720
Some people make tea with rose petals, and others put them in salads.

30:25.720 --> 30:28.720
Flowers and perfumes.

30:28.720 --> 30:43.720
People make wonderful perfumes with flowers like roses, jasmine, violets, lilacs, orange blossoms, red tulips and peonies.

30:43.720 --> 30:49.720
Chapter 6, The Sisters Plan

30:49.720 --> 30:55.720
The next morning, Beauty wakes up in her bedroom in her father's house.

30:55.720 --> 30:58.720
She gets up and goes downstairs.

30:58.720 --> 31:01.720
When her father sees her, he cries.

31:01.720 --> 31:03.720
Beauty, is that you?

31:03.720 --> 31:05.720
How wonderful.

31:05.720 --> 31:07.720
My daughter is well and she's here.

31:07.720 --> 31:11.720
Beauty is very happy and hugs her father.

31:11.720 --> 31:15.720
Get dressed quickly and then tell me about the beast.

31:15.720 --> 31:17.720
Says her father happily.

31:17.720 --> 31:23.720
She goes to her room and finds a chest full of beautiful clothes.

31:23.720 --> 31:26.720
This is a present from the beast.

31:26.720 --> 31:28.720
Says Beauty to her father.

31:28.720 --> 31:32.720
He's very nice and gives me presents every day.

31:32.720 --> 31:35.720
She chooses some lovely clothes.

31:35.720 --> 31:39.720
I want to give these lovely clothes to Rosalind and Hortensia.

31:39.720 --> 31:44.720
She says, when she says this, the chest disappears.

31:44.720 --> 31:47.720
The beast is watching you.

31:47.720 --> 31:49.720
Says Beauty's father.

31:49.720 --> 31:53.720
These beautiful clothes are for you and not for your sisters.

31:53.720 --> 31:57.720
Suddenly, the chest comes back again.

31:57.720 --> 32:02.720
That morning, Rosalind and Hortensia come to visit their sister.

32:02.720 --> 32:05.720
They are both very unhappy.

32:05.720 --> 32:07.720
Oh, Beauty.

32:07.720 --> 32:08.720
Says Rosalind.

32:08.720 --> 32:10.720
I'm unhappy.

32:10.720 --> 32:12.720
Why are you unhappy Rosalind?

32:12.720 --> 32:14.720
Asks Beauty.

32:14.720 --> 32:16.720
Oh, it's a long story.

32:16.720 --> 32:18.720
Says Rosalind.

32:18.720 --> 32:19.720
Please tell me.

32:19.720 --> 32:20.720
Says Beauty.

32:20.720 --> 32:25.720
My husband is handsome and he spends all day in front of a mirror.

32:25.720 --> 32:29.720
He never looks at me or talks to me.

32:29.720 --> 32:32.720
Oh dear, that's a big problem.

32:32.720 --> 32:34.720
Says Beauty.

32:34.720 --> 32:36.720
Hortensia says,

32:36.720 --> 32:39.720
My husband is very clever.

32:39.720 --> 32:43.720
But he doesn't like anyone and no one likes him.

32:43.720 --> 32:49.720
I can never invite my friends to lunch or dinner because he doesn't like them.

32:49.720 --> 32:52.720
We've got a lot of problems with our husbands.

32:52.720 --> 32:54.720
They say.

32:54.720 --> 32:56.720
My poor sisters.

32:56.720 --> 32:57.720
Says Beauty.

32:57.720 --> 32:59.720
I'm very sorry.

32:59.720 --> 33:02.720
Tell us about the beast.

33:02.720 --> 33:04.720
Says Hortensia.

33:04.720 --> 33:06.720
Oh, the beast is not a bad man.

33:06.720 --> 33:07.720
Says Beauty.

33:07.720 --> 33:09.720
He's very kind.

33:09.720 --> 33:13.720
I live in his beautiful castle and I'm the queen.

33:13.720 --> 33:15.720
I don't work.

33:15.720 --> 33:16.720
I read.

33:16.720 --> 33:19.720
Play the piano and walk in the garden.

33:19.720 --> 33:25.720
Every evening the beast comes to see me at dinner and we talk about a lot of things.

33:25.720 --> 33:27.720
It's wonderful.

33:27.720 --> 33:32.720
The two sisters are very angry and they go to the garden.

33:32.720 --> 33:36.720
Beauty wears lovely clothes and shoes.

33:36.720 --> 33:37.720
Says Rosalind.

33:37.720 --> 33:39.720
She's like a queen.

33:39.720 --> 33:41.720
She's very happy.

33:41.720 --> 33:45.720
Why is she lucky and why are we unlucky?

33:45.720 --> 33:49.720
You're right Rosalind, says Hortensia.

33:49.720 --> 33:51.720
We are not very lucky.

33:51.720 --> 33:54.720
But maybe we can be lucky.

33:54.720 --> 34:01.720
Beauty has to return to the beast in a week or he's going to get angry and eat her.

34:01.720 --> 34:04.720
Then we must keep her here.

34:04.720 --> 34:05.720
Says Rosalind.

34:05.720 --> 34:08.720
Then the beast is going to get angry.

34:08.720 --> 34:12.720
During the week the two sisters are kind to beauty.

34:12.720 --> 34:14.720
They talk and laugh with her.

34:14.720 --> 34:17.720
They walk together in the country.

34:17.720 --> 34:20.720
Beauty is happy with her sisters.

34:20.720 --> 34:23.720
Rosalind and Hortensia love me.

34:23.720 --> 34:24.720
Beauty thinks.

34:24.720 --> 34:29.720
They're good sisters and I love them a lot.

34:29.720 --> 34:32.720
At the end of the week beauty says.

34:32.720 --> 34:35.720
I must go back to the beast's castle.

34:35.720 --> 34:38.720
But her sisters start to cry.

34:38.720 --> 34:40.720
Oh, oh, Beauty.

34:40.720 --> 34:41.720
Says Rosalind.

34:41.720 --> 34:43.720
Please stay with us another week.

34:43.720 --> 34:45.720
We need you.

34:45.720 --> 34:47.720
Yes Beauty.

34:47.720 --> 34:49.720
Says Hortensia.

34:49.720 --> 34:51.720
Please don't leave us.

34:51.720 --> 34:54.720
We have fun with you and we love you.

34:54.720 --> 34:55.720
Yes.

34:55.720 --> 34:56.720
Says Rosalind.

34:56.720 --> 34:58.720
Stay with us.

34:58.720 --> 35:01.720
We can do a lot of things together.

35:01.720 --> 35:04.720
Beauty does not know what to do.

35:04.720 --> 35:08.720
She decides to stay another week.

35:11.720 --> 35:12.720
Chapter seven.

35:12.720 --> 35:14.720
The dream.

35:14.720 --> 35:19.720
The beast is going to be very sad without me.

35:19.720 --> 35:20.720
Beauty thinks.

35:20.720 --> 35:24.720
But I want to stay with my family for a few more days.

35:24.720 --> 35:27.720
Then I'm going to go back to him.

35:27.720 --> 35:29.720
Beauty thinks about the beast.

35:29.720 --> 35:31.720
She misses him.

35:31.720 --> 35:36.720
Ten days later beauty dreams about the beast.

35:36.720 --> 35:40.720
In her dream the beast is on the grass in the garden of the castle.

35:40.720 --> 35:42.720
And he's going to die.

35:42.720 --> 35:44.720
Beauty.

35:44.720 --> 35:46.720
Wispers the beast.

35:46.720 --> 35:50.720
Today is the tenth day and you're not here.

35:50.720 --> 35:53.720
I can't live without you.

35:53.720 --> 35:56.720
I can't eat or drink.

35:56.720 --> 35:59.720
Beauty wakes up and thinks.

35:59.720 --> 36:03.720
The poor beast is going to die without me.

36:03.720 --> 36:05.720
I must go back to him.

36:05.720 --> 36:10.720
She takes the ring and puts it on a table near her bed.

36:10.720 --> 36:14.720
The beast is ugly but he's very kind.

36:14.720 --> 36:15.720
She thinks.

36:15.720 --> 36:17.720
Why don't I marry him?

36:17.720 --> 36:19.720
I'm happy with him.

36:19.720 --> 36:24.720
My sisters have handsome clever husbands but they're not happy.

36:25.720 --> 36:31.720
Beauty falls asleep and the next morning she wakes up at the beast's castle.

36:31.720 --> 36:35.720
Today I'm going to wear a beautiful dress.

36:35.720 --> 36:37.720
Beauty thinks.

36:37.720 --> 36:42.720
At nine o'clock in the evening she goes to dinner and waits for the beast.

36:42.720 --> 36:45.720
But he doesn't come to see her.

36:45.720 --> 36:46.720
What's happening?

36:46.720 --> 36:48.720
Beauty thinks.

36:48.720 --> 36:49.720
Where's the beast?

36:49.720 --> 36:52.720
Why isn't he here?

36:52.720 --> 36:53.720
Beast!

36:53.720 --> 36:55.720
She cries.

36:55.720 --> 36:56.720
Beast!

36:56.720 --> 36:58.720
Where are you?

36:58.720 --> 37:00.720
Answer me!

37:00.720 --> 37:05.720
She opens the doors of all the rooms and looks everywhere in the castle.

37:05.720 --> 37:07.720
But she cannot find him.

37:07.720 --> 37:10.720
Suddenly she remembers her dream.

37:10.720 --> 37:14.720
She runs to the garden and sees the beast on the grass.

37:14.720 --> 37:15.720
Oh no!

37:15.720 --> 37:16.720
She cries.

37:16.720 --> 37:18.720
Is he dead?

37:18.720 --> 37:21.720
She listens to his heart and it is beating.

37:21.720 --> 37:22.720
Good.

37:22.720 --> 37:23.720
He's not dead.

37:23.720 --> 37:24.720
She thinks.

37:24.720 --> 37:29.720
She gets some cold water from the river and wets his face.

37:29.720 --> 37:33.720
The beast slowly opens his eyes.

37:33.720 --> 37:34.720
Beauty.

37:34.720 --> 37:36.720
He whispers.

37:36.720 --> 37:38.720
I'm dying.

37:39.720 --> 37:41.720
But I'm happy.

37:41.720 --> 37:42.720
Because you're here.

37:42.720 --> 37:44.720
No beast!

37:44.720 --> 37:45.720
Crys beauty.

37:45.720 --> 37:46.720
Don't die.

37:46.720 --> 37:49.720
You must live and become my husband.

37:49.720 --> 37:53.720
I love you and I can't live without you.

37:56.720 --> 37:58.720
Chapter 8.

37:58.720 --> 38:00.720
The Prince.

38:00.720 --> 38:05.720
Suddenly all the lights of the castle and the garden turn on.

38:05.720 --> 38:08.720
There are beautiful fireworks in the sky.

38:08.720 --> 38:12.720
Beauty is surprised and looks at the castle.

38:12.720 --> 38:15.720
Then she turns round and looks at the beast.

38:15.720 --> 38:17.720
What a surprise!

38:17.720 --> 38:20.720
She sees a handsome young man.

38:20.720 --> 38:22.720
Thank you beauty.

38:22.720 --> 38:24.720
Says the young man.

38:24.720 --> 38:26.720
The spell is broken.

38:26.720 --> 38:29.720
But where is the beast?

38:29.720 --> 38:30.720
Asks beauty.

38:30.720 --> 38:32.720
I am the beast.

38:32.720 --> 38:34.720
Says the prince.

38:34.720 --> 38:36.720
I don't understand.

38:36.720 --> 38:37.720
Says beauty.

38:37.720 --> 38:38.720
Who are you?

38:38.720 --> 38:40.720
I'm a prince.

38:40.720 --> 38:42.720
And this is my castle.

38:42.720 --> 38:44.720
Says the young man.

38:44.720 --> 38:48.720
Sometimes a bad witch puts a spell on a prince.

38:48.720 --> 38:52.720
And only true love can break the spell.

38:52.720 --> 38:55.720
Now I know your love is true.

38:55.720 --> 38:59.720
The prince takes her hand and says.

38:59.720 --> 39:02.720
Do you want to marry me beauty?

39:02.720 --> 39:06.720
Beauty looks at the handsome prince and says.

39:06.720 --> 39:08.720
Yes I do.

39:08.720 --> 39:12.720
Beauty and the prince go to the castle.

39:12.720 --> 39:15.720
When she opens the door she is surprised.

39:15.720 --> 39:17.720
My family.

39:17.720 --> 39:18.720
You're all here.

39:18.720 --> 39:20.720
Christ beauty.

39:20.720 --> 39:23.720
She is happy when she sees her family.

39:23.720 --> 39:26.720
They talk and laugh together.

39:26.720 --> 39:30.720
Suddenly she sees the good fairy from her dream.

39:30.720 --> 39:31.720
Beauty.

39:31.720 --> 39:33.720
Says the good fairy.

39:33.720 --> 39:35.720
You've got a kind heart.

39:35.720 --> 39:40.720
And you're going to marry the prince and become a princess.

39:40.720 --> 39:44.720
Then the good fairy looks at beauty's two sisters.

39:44.720 --> 39:48.720
You're both bad, lazy and unkind.

39:48.720 --> 39:49.720
Says the fairy.

39:49.720 --> 39:52.720
You don't love anyone.

39:52.720 --> 39:54.720
The fairy says some magic words.

39:54.720 --> 39:58.720
And suddenly Rosalind and Hortensia become statues.

39:59.720 --> 40:00.720
Oh no.

40:00.720 --> 40:01.720
Christ beauty.

40:01.720 --> 40:04.720
My sisters are statues.

40:04.720 --> 40:07.720
Your sisters have got hearts of stone.

40:07.720 --> 40:08.720
Says the fairy.

40:08.720 --> 40:10.720
Now they can't move.

40:10.720 --> 40:13.720
But they can see and hear everything.

40:13.720 --> 40:21.720
When they understand their mistakes they can become Rosalind and Hortensia again.

40:21.720 --> 40:25.720
The next day beauty and the prince get married.

40:25.720 --> 40:28.720
Everyone dances and sings in the castle.

40:28.720 --> 40:30.720
It is a happy day.

40:30.720 --> 40:34.720
People give flowers to beauty and the prince.

40:34.720 --> 40:38.720
The prince sees tears in beauty's eyes and says...

40:38.720 --> 40:41.720
Don't cry my beauty.

40:41.720 --> 40:44.720
We are going to be very happy together.

